</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3261DE06661FFF81984FB7EFDFFEA18" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B834E6B6661FFF81984FB7EFDFFEA18" blockId="5.[192,778,1099,1637]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="B94892796661FFF81984FB7EFE82E898" box="[240,347,1229,1253]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Remarks</emphasis>
. Aside from this record, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C35E86661FFF81B0CFB7DFD02E898" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1820" box="[632,731,1230,1253]" class="Diplopoda" family="Spirobolidae" genus="Narceus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirobolida" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94892796661FFF81B0CFB7DFD02E898" box="[632,731,1230,1253]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Narceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has never been reported from 
<collectingRegion id="49F880896661FFF81B73FB5EFD57E978" box="[519,654,1261,1285]" country="United States of America" name="Minnesota" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Minnesota</collectingRegion>
, although localities in 
<collectingRegion id="49F880896661FFF8182DFABEFE01E958" box="[345,472,1293,1317]" country="United States of America" name="Wisconsin" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Wisconsin</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49F880896661FFF81B6CFABEFD8DE959" box="[536,596,1293,1316]" country="United States of America" name="Iowa" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Iowa</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD339A6661FFF81B11FABEFCDFE958" author="Keeton, W. T." box="[613,774,1293,1317]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 146" refId="ref14573" refString="Keeton, W. T. 1960. A taxonomic study of the milliped family Spirobolidae (Diplopoda: Spirobolida). Memoirs of the American Entomological Society 17: 1 - 146." type="journal article" year="1960">Keeton 1960</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD339A6661FFF819B4FA9EFE77E938" author="Watermolen, D. J." box="[192,430,1325,1349]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="225 - 226" refId="ref16698" refString="Watermolen, D. J. 1995 a. Distribution of the milliped Narceus americanus annularis (Spirobolida: Spirobolidae) in Wisconsin. Great Lakes Entomologist 28 (3 - 4): 225 - 226." type="journal article" year="1995">Watermolen 1995a</bibRefCitation>
, b; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD339A6661FFF818ADFA9EFD18E938" author="Shelley, R. M. &amp; C. T. McAllister &amp; M. F. Medrano" box="[473,705,1325,1349]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="374 - 389" refId="ref16292" refString="Shelley, R. M., C. T. McAllister, and M. F. Medrano. 2006. Distribution of the milliped genus Narceus Rafinesque, 1820 (Spirobolida: Spirobolidae): Occurrences in New England and west of the Mississippi River; a summary of peripheral localities; and first records from Connecticut, Delaware, Maine, and Minnesota. Western North American Naturalist 66 (3): 374 - 389." type="journal article" year="2006">Shelley et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
) indicate occurrence in the southeast along the 
<collectingRegion id="49F880896661FFF81BA6FAFEFEC7E9F8" country="United States of America" name="Mississippi" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Mississippi</collectingRegion>
River. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD339A6661FFF81801FADEFDBEE9F8" author="Shelley, R. M. &amp; C. T. McAllister &amp; M. F. Medrano" box="[373,615,1389,1413]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="374 - 389" refId="ref16292" refString="Shelley, R. M., C. T. McAllister, and M. F. Medrano. 2006. Distribution of the milliped genus Narceus Rafinesque, 1820 (Spirobolida: Spirobolidae): Occurrences in New England and west of the Mississippi River; a summary of peripheral localities; and first records from Connecticut, Delaware, Maine, and Minnesota. Western North American Naturalist 66 (3): 374 - 389." type="journal article" year="2006">Shelley et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
thought that it might represent an allopatric population and suggested occurrence in the eastern fringe of 
<collectingRegion id="49F880896661FFF819B4FA7EFEB1E998" box="[192,360,1485,1509]" country="United States of America" name="South Dakota" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">South Dakota</collectingRegion>
, which still seems plausible though we did not encounter the milliped. Gonopodal, cyphopodal, and somatic illustrations are available in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD339A6661FFF81867F99EFE63EA38" author="Keeton, W. T." box="[275,442,1581,1605]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 146" refId="ref14573" refString="Keeton, W. T. 1960. A taxonomic study of the milliped family Spirobolidae (Diplopoda: Spirobolida). Memoirs of the American Entomological Society 17: 1 - 146." type="journal article" year="1960">Keeton (1960)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD339A6661FFF818B7F99EFDBDEA38" author="Shelley, R. M." box="[451,612,1581,1605]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="37 - 79" refId="ref15492" refString="Shelley, R. M. 1978. Millipeds of the eastern Piedmont region of North Carolina, U. S. A. (Diplopoda). Journal of Natural History 12: 37 - 79." type="journal article" year="1978">Shelley (1978</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD339A6661FFF81B19F99EFD70EA38" author="Shelley, R. M." box="[621,681,1581,1605]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="1638 - 1663" refId="ref15671" refString="Shelley, R. M. 1988. The millipeds of eastern Canada (Arthropoda: Diplopoda). Canadian Journal of Zoology 66: 1638 - 1663." type="journal article" year="1988">1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD339A6661FFF81BC6F99EFD27EA38" author="Shelley, R. M." box="[690,766,1581,1605]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="25 - 29" refId="ref15988" refString="Shelley, R. M. 2002 b. Narceus woodruffi Causey, a forgotten milliped species (Spirobolida: Spirobolidae). Insecta Mundi 16 (1 - 3): 25 - 29." type="journal article" year="2002">2002b</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD339A6661FFF81980F9FEFDFAEA18" author="Filka, M. E. &amp; R. M. Shelley" box="[244,547,1613,1637]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 42" refId="ref14085" refString="Filka, M. E., and R. M. Shelley. 1980. The milliped fauna of the Kings Mountain region of North Carolina (Arthropoda: Diplopoda). Brimleyana 4: 1 - 42." type="journal article" year="1980">Filka and Shelley (1980)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
